1. Is pragma = version control?
      It tells the compiler:
           Use this version (or range of versions) to compile this contract
Why specifically the word "pragma"?
  The word “pragma” comes from “pragmatic”, meaning:
             Practical instruction for the compiler

So:
It is used for compiler-related settings
Not for variables, functions, or logic

Is pragma permanent?
 "No"
    It only affects compilation
    Once compiled, the smart contract bytecode is fixed on blockchain

So:
It does NOT exist inside the blockchain
It only helps during development
