What is a Struct?
Definition:
    A struct is a way to group multiple variables into one.

Simple idea:
Like a student record
One student has:
name
age
marks
Instead of creating separate variables, we group them.
syntax:
    struct variable_name{
        declaration
    }
example :
    struct Student {
    string name;
    uint age;
}

Inside a struct, what do we write?

✔️ Inside a struct, you only declare variables (properties)
❌ You do NOT write functions or logic

Struct creates a custom data type.
Like how uint is a built-in type,
struct lets YOU create your own type.
