Return Values (Very Clear)
Example:
    string greeting = "Hello";

function sayHello() public returns (string memory) {
    return greeting;
}

What is happening?
returns (string memory)
→ “This function will give back a string”
return greeting;
→ sends "Hello" back
👉 Simple idea:
     Function gives output


Three Types of Functions (MOST IMPORTANT)
 There are 3 types 👇
          1.Normal function
          2.view function
          3.pure function

     1.Normal Function
          function changeData() public {
              greeting = "Hi";
         }

               This:
                 Changes data ✅
               Example:
                   Like editing your profile name ✏️

     2.view function
         function sayHello() public view returns (string memory) {
                return greeting;
          }
               This:
                  Only reads data 👀
                  Does NOT change anything ❌
               Example:
                    Checking your bank balance 💰
     3.pure function 
          function multiply(uint a, uint b) public pure returns (uint) {
                return a * b;
          }
                 This:
                     Does NOT read data ❌
                     Does NOT change data ❌
                     Only uses inputs
                 Example:
                        Calculator 🧮

| Function Type | Reads Data | Changes Data |
| ------------- | ---------- | ------------ |
| Normal        | ✅          | ✅            |
| view          | ✅          | ❌            |
| pure          | ❌          | ❌            |
