What is keccak256?
  Simple meaning:
         It converts input → into a random-looking number
      example : 
             keccak256(abi.encodePacked("aaaab"));

             "aaaab" ------------>This is just input data (string)
          abi.encodePacked------------>Convert "aaaab" into bytes format   (because keccak256  only accepts bytes)

          keccak256(...)
              This is also syntax, but meaning is:
              Take input → generate hash (random-like number)
